2. The vehicle is launched into leo as the third stage <br>
of A Saturn 5, or Energia class chemical rocket.<br>
3.The vehicle has 3/1 mass ratio<br>
4. 2/3 of the vehicles mass is Loh<br>
5. The vehicle is powered by (4)  35 kw nuclear fission <br>
reactors. Each reactor weighs 1500 pounds and generates<br>
35,000 watts of electric power.<br>
6. The 160,000 pounds of Loh is stored in one <br>
32000 pound titanium metal tank that is insulated by kevlar.<br>
7.A nitrogen 14 pressure feed pump pumps the Loh into an electric arc jet engine at the   rate of 24 grams per second.<br>
8. The arc jet engine has a specific impulse of 1000 seconds,<br>
and its is made mostly of titanium metal .<br>
9.The arc jet engine zaps the 24 grams of Loh with a 120 kw<br>
electric discharge between an anode, and a cathode.<br>
10. The electric current running through the plasma causes<br>
the plasma to generate a magnetic confinement field around itself.<br>
11.The Loh is heated to 2500 C and explelled though a 45 degree  converging/diverging titanium delaval nozzle.<br>
12. The 24 grams of 2500 C hydrogen plasma is expelled at<br>
30,000 feet per second which is 10 kilometers /sec.<br>
  13. The 24 gram plasma exchaust beam generates a thrust <br>
of  1,584 pounds.<br>
14. This thrust accelerates the mars ship at the rate<br>
of .066 Gs.<br>
15. The engine must fire for 5000 seconds in order to accelerate the ship by 3000 meters per second.<br>
16.The ship already has 9000 meter/sec in leo.<br>
17. 9000 + 3000 = 12,000 meters second which is <br>
25,777 miles per hour + 1000 miles per hour from the earths east west rotation.<br>
18. The ship will leave earth at 26,777 miles per hour.<br>
19.The earth will take back 24,600 miles per hour from the pull of its gravity.<br>
20. THis will leave a hyperbolic excess velocity relative to the earth of 2,177 miles per hour.<br>
21. This will add to the the velocity of the earth around the <br>
sun which is 66,000 miles per hour.<br>
22.The ship will head for mars at about 68,177 miles per hour relative to the sun.<br>
23. When the ship reaches mars the pull of the suns gravity<br>
will have slowed it down to about 47,000 miles per hour.<br>
24.The average velocity on the trip relative to the sun will<br>
be 47000 + 68000 = 115,000 devided by two which is<br>
58,000 miles per hour. Flighttime will be about 6-8 months<br>
to reach mars.(180-240 days)<br>
25. When the ship approaches mars it will fire the arc jet<br>
engine for 5050 seconds in order to shed 10,000 feet per second. <br>
26. It will then go into orbit around the planet mars.<br>
27.It will stay there for several months until the alignment of the planets is right to return to earth.<br>
28. Then it will fire the arc jet engine for 2479 more seconds to escape from mars orbit, and then return to earth.<br>
29. On return to earth it will  will fire the arc jet engine <br>
until all remainng propellant is gone in order to slow it down<br>
enough to be captured by earths gravity and  go into<br>
 earth orbit. It wil approach the earth at about 68,000 miles an hour relative to the sun.<br>
30. Then the craft can refilled with more Loh by a tanker<br>
rocket or tanker rockets in leo . and then  take a new trip<br>
 to mars. This ship is reusable. If you add some clip on tanks<br>
to increase the mass ratio, and fire the arc jet engine longer<br>
this craft can also travel to jupiter saturn and all the outer<br>
planets. It would take 2.5 years to reach Jupiter, and<br>
about 5 years to reach Saturn . Pluto could reached within<br>
not more then 12 years flght time.<br>
31. This ship has a 3 person crew.<br>
32. It can carry out the equivelent of the Apollo 8<br>
mission to orbit the moon in December 1968 by orbiting mars.<br>
33. Large versions of this ship , or multiple stage versions of this ship can be mafe by docking multiple 120 ton modules togetherin leo of the above design.A largeer, and heavier version of this ship could land people on mars for a period of several ,months.At 10,000 dollars per pound it would cost<br>
2,400,000,000 dollars to orbit mars for several months with a crewed ship. A landing on Phobos, and Deimos might be done as part of this initial mars orbital expedition.<br>
